  "title": "[connectSortBy] avoid to throw an error when the index does not exist",
  "body": "**Describe the bug 🐛**\r\n\r\nThe current implementation does throw an error when the current index is not in the list of provided indices. It can be an issue with the URL sync. It's easy for a users to mistyped the name of the index. The errors throw and block the render of the InstantSearch App.\r\n\r\n> https://rrz1pyz83n.codesandbox.io/?sortBy=instantt_search_price_asc\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior 💭**\r\n\r\nFallback to the default index when the current one does not exist?\r\n\r\n**Additional context**\r\n\r\n> https://discourse.algolia.com/t/how-to-catch-errors/6938\r\n",
